</title>
<subSubSection id="90B6B2E305DDEBB5BF53A30014EA15BC" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" type="description">
<paragraph id="8076F967CBDEC446104FE9EF365E1717" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="D0424375ABECB1A7120021B480DFCC4B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Centaurea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D1224337EA11ACE6A0E35A7128068641" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Centaurea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(S. 436) durch folgende Merkmale: 
<emphasis id="AE4C9AAC828CDABA81B54E7D44C0544A" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
<taxonomicName id="B0863EE860F604F7F0394803DCE6A7A6" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pappus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pappus</taxonomicName>
bedeutend 
<normalizedToken id="A9DB7A72A6657EC0F019500C10E013BD" originalValue="länger" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">laenger</normalizedToken>
als die Frucht, als Ganzes abfallend
</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="6D189EE668F26566D0085729C7680A16" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
am Grunde 
<normalizedToken id="77AE98356C75BC32864D0E5258D3816B" originalValue="ringförmig" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">ringfoermig</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="5FFEBE28D15DB5806D5EB4ABCC724F5D" originalValue="zusammenhängend" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">zusammenhaengend</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
), 
<emphasis id="2D11730A9BEE97E66E4B353933E29CA5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">mit federartig behaarten Borsten</emphasis>
(Haare 2-5mal so lang wie die Dicke der Borste).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="784C589A43501251D5F78DCA916A43CD" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
Die Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="1CB126A52D367E4FE9819E887FCB1AC9" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leuzea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="42A778EE180C83FECD4F300E82FE1FFF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Leuzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken id="CA633C3FFAF2CF3D799833E482E3438D" originalValue="umfaßt" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">umfasst</normalizedToken>
etwa 
<emphasis id="726CBCD2CFF00A2F466801BF71D00DE5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">10 Arten</emphasis>
und ist verbreitet vom 
<emphasis id="9ADABA5F12291D23107499F98A82B50E" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Mittelmeergebiet bis Ostasien;</emphasis>
je 1 Art in Australien und in Chile. Nach Dittrich (1968a) 
<normalizedToken id="313E50897702C8701740C3FEE1EA4A19" originalValue="müssen" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">muessen</normalizedToken>
die meisten Arten der Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="2458F47F8E7808DF7C6535C742C488A3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leuzea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="BA1042EA84175BA2BAFECF826A0D7A70" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Leuzea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
zur Gattung 
<taxonomicName id="454DDBA22F5EE30B858D5D11C4A59172" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Rhaponticum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="04A112BAFF7BA16937D53CFBBFD212D5" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Rhaponticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gestellt werden. Ob 
<taxonomicName id="65EDD0C4139A7BCD717EC2F29764ADCF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Leuzea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,IPNI" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="conifera">
<emphasis id="8668967CFE457A9D7D922A184D9FE165" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
<authorityName id="89B83A304798CA2BE2037194224A6454" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">L.</authorityName>
conifera
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
durch ihren 
<emphasis id="4DFA9F90BF2A51C5D1EA8C316F6E1ACE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">
1reihigen 
<taxonomicName id="15F95CBD13FF53E74426E20C4BB645C7" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Pappus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Pappus</taxonomicName>
und die warzigen 
<normalizedToken id="FDE1F9C6F5F06E901F774195B36C7FF5" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
eindeutig von 
<taxonomicName id="723639EB39437EDA4464035C428BCCC3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Rhaponticum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="null" pageNumber="436" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6BE5A84C12735F563C63527DBB6875DE" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">Rhaponticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
abgetrennt werden kann, 
<normalizedToken id="E79973E7855834D7FD1B4195AEE2B41D" originalValue="muß" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">muss</normalizedToken>
<normalizedToken id="E9D081069039019D7DCE92A09C1828D9" originalValue="abgeklärt" pageId="null" pageNumber="436">abgeklaert</normalizedToken>
werden.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
